Beijing health authorities confirmed the city's first case of the highly contagious Omicron variant of COVID-19 on Saturday. "A total of 15 close contacts have been traced and put into quarantine," Pang Xinghuo, deputy director of the Beijing center for disease control and prevention, told a press conference. "The individual has no contact with any confirmed cases and hasn't left the city within 14 days," Pang added. The patient had a sore throat on Thursday and developed a fever the next day. Two people living with the case were tested negative. Disinfection has been conducted at their residential community and an epidemiological investigation is underway.